        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 19" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:10:24 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="19">
        <outline text="Using Codex to optimize the site-id attributes in Baseline" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:10:25 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="The attributes are currently added directly in the PHP templates for the content" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:10:59 GMT">
            <outline text="There are separate PHP templates for singular and titled posts, so it appears twice" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:11:39 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="I opened codex in the theme directory, and pointed it to testing.js and https://daveverse.org" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:12:18 GMT"/>
          <outline text="It proposed adding the site-id markup to the post-id plugin" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:13:07 GMT"/>
          <outline text="It also proposed a set of rules for the theme to make sure testing.js will continue to work" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:40 GMT"/>
          <outline text="## WordLand Reply Markup Contract" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:41 GMT">
            <outline text="Dave's reply JavaScript, currently loaded from `https://s3.amazonaws.com/scripting.com/code/baselineplayground/testing.js`, depends on a small set of frontend markup conventions:" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:43 GMT"/>
            <outline text="1. The page must include `#wordland-siteId` with a usable `data-siteId` value." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:44 GMT"/>
            <outline text="2. Each replyable post permalink must use `.spPermaLink` and `data-postid`." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:44 GMT"/>
            <outline text="3. The `.spPermaLink` element must contain an anchor whose `href` is the post permalink or day-archive anchor permalink." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:44 GMT"/>
            <outline text="4. Titled posts should place the permalink span inside `.divStoryTitle`." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:44 GMT"/>
            <outline text="5. Singular posts should place the permalink span at the end of the final content paragraph, so it remains the last content span before the reply script appends its icon." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:45 GMT"/>
            <outline text="The expected singular-post permalink shape is:" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:45 GMT"/>
            <outline text="&lt;p&gt;Post body &lt;span class=&quot;spPermaLink&quot; data-postid=&quot;123&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://example.com/2026/04/18/#a123&quot; title=&quot;Direct link to this item.&quot;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:45 GMT"/>
            <outline text="Themes may style `.spPermaLink`, but should not rename the class, remove `data-postid`, or move the singular permalink outside the final paragraph unless the reply JavaScript is updated at the same time." created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:34:46 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2026 10:48:49 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 17" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:05:34 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="17">
        <outline text="Dave, thanks for the mention on Scripting News!" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:05:35 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="This was actually my first time working with Codex" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:05:49 GMT">
            <outline text="I already had the basic code to put the site-id into the dom in a WordPress site" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:08:01 GMT">
              <outline text="With help for the standard ChatGPT app" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:13:59 GMT"/>
              <outline text="It's pretty good with PHP and WordPress, since both have a long documented history " created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:14:21 GMT"/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Codex helped to package the code into a GitHub repo that others can use" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:08:49 GMT"/>
          </outline>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 12" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:13:17 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="12">
        <outline text="Inspired by Dave's experience with coding agents, I've installed a local agent for the first time" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:13:18 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="Codex, since I already have a OpenAI subscription" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:14:44 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Until now I've been using the chat window in VS Code, I also tried out Windsurf for a few months" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:15:21 GMT"/>
          <outline text="My first project was to make the WordLand Site ID plugin into a properly documented GitHub repo" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:21:57 GMT">
            <outline text="It was just a one-off PHP file that was only installed on https://daveverse.org" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:23:00 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="I then pointed it to https://this.how/wordland/, and asked for a one-liner to explain how the siteID related to WordLand" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:29:28 GMT">
            <outline text="It suggested: The site ID is used by [WordLand](https://this.how/wordland/) to connect WordPress sites to WordLand experiences. " created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:30:14 GMT"/>
            <outline text="That's not a bad suggestion 😃" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:30:52 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Repo now up at https://github.com/scotthansonde/wordland-site-id" created="Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:54:14 GMT" type="link" url="https://github.com/scotthansonde/wordland-site-id"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 11" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:12:38 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="11">
        <outline text="Setting up plugins for MultiSite" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:12:39 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="Plugins can either be required for all subsites (&quot;Network Activated&quot;) or optional" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:12:52 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Subsites cannot install their own plugins, that's a restriction of Multisite" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:19:40 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Proposed required plugins" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:13:25 GMT">
            <outline text="Jetpack" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:13:35 GMT"/>
            <outline text="Baseline CSS and JS Loader" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:13:37 GMT">
              <outline text="This pulls testing.css and testing.js from https://s3.amazonaws.com/scripting.com/code/baselineplayground/" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:15:02 GMT"/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="RSS Cloud External Ping" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:15:58 GMT"/>
            <outline text="Markdown RSS" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:19:09 GMT"/>
            <outline text="WordLand Site ID" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:16:35 GMT">
              <outline text="This adds the siteid to the dom" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:16:46 GMT"/>
            </outline>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Proposed optional plugins" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:19:22 GMT">
            <outline text="Activity Pub" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:20:14 GMT"/>
            <outline text="FeedLand Blogroll" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 16:20:59 GMT"/>
          </outline>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 10" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:03:47 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="10">
        <outline text="Next step, site creation API" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:03:48 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="ChatGPT suggested writing our own API in nodejs that connects to WP-CLI to create sites" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:04:08 GMT">
            <outline text="https://wp-cli.org/" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:05:45 GMT" type="link" url="https://wp-cli.org/"/>
            <outline text="&quot;WP-CLI is the command-line interface for WordPress. You can update plugins, configure multisite installations and much more, without using a web browser.&quot;" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:06:26 GMT"/>
            <outline text="WP-CLI is basically WordPress running from the command line, so it needs access to the same files and database as the web app. It can only run remotely via ssh. " created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:12:32 GMT"/>
            <outline text="Actually ChatGPT suggested an API in python. I asked it to do it in nodejs instead." created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 15:51:29 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Together we wrote a small nodejs app for an api that adds new sites via WP-CLI" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:13:18 GMT">
            <outline text="Example request" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:18:56 GMT">
              <outline text="curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/sites \" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:19:07 GMT">
                <outline text="-H &quot;Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_TOKEN&quot; \"/>
                <outline text="-H &quot;Content-Type: application/json&quot; \"/>
                <outline text="-d '{" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:19:22 GMT">
                  <outline text="&quot;slug&quot;: &quot;client1&quot;,"/>
                  <outline text="&quot;title&quot;: &quot;Client 1&quot;,"/>
                  <outline text="&quot;email&quot;: &quot;admin@example.com&quot;"/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="}'" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:19:16 GMT"/>
              </outline>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Response on success" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:19:51 GMT">
              <outline text="{" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:20:14 GMT">
                <outline text="&quot;success&quot;: true,"/>
                <outline text="&quot;domain&quot;: &quot;client1.example.com&quot;,"/>
                <outline text="&quot;siteId&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,"/>
                <outline text="&quot;message&quot;: &quot;Site created successfully&quot;"/>
              </outline>
              <outline text="}" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:20:34 GMT"/>
            </outline>
          </outline>
          <outline text="curl call works on localhost (created https://client2.wpzz.de/)" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:42:46 GMT"/>
          <outline text="set up https://provisioner.wpzz.de/ in Caddy and it works from anywhere (created https://client3.wpzz.de/)" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:43:03 GMT"/>
          <outline text="https://provisioner.wpzz.de/health returns ok, even without auth" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:43:41 GMT" type="link" url="https://provisioner.wpzz.de/health"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 9" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:36:56 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="09">
        <outline text="I get an error trying to listen to the voicemail" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:55:52 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="The error message" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:58:02 GMT">
            <outline text="The recording could not be found. Try using another account if you think this is an error." created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:56:18 GMT"/>
            <outline text="You're currently signed in as papascott@gmail.com" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:56:29 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="I would be very interested in hearing this" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:58:17 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Update: it's working, I'm listening right now 😃" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:58:37 GMT"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Setting the Baseline theme for new sites" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:36:57 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="It's not as straightforward as I had hoped" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:37:11 GMT"/>
          <outline text="The setting WP_DEFAULT_THEME needs to match the theme directory name exactly " created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:37:32 GMT"/>
          <outline text="If we install release files from github, the directory is named after the zip file name" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:38:04 GMT">
            <outline text="Which includes the version number, so the directory name will change each time" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:38:41 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Luckily ChatGPT proposed a plugin to use the theme named &quot;Wordland Baseline&quot; set in styles.css" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:39:24 GMT"/>
          <outline text="We just have to be careful we don't install multiple versions of the theme" created="Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:40:17 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 8" created="Wed, 08 Apr 2026 16:34:31 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="08">
        <outline text="Basic functionality for Multisite WordPress is working" created="Wed, 08 Apr 2026 16:34:32 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="Main site: https://wpzz.de" created="Wed, 08 Apr 2026 16:34:48 GMT" type="link" url="https://wpzz.de"/>
          <outline text="First subsite: https://firstpost.wpzz.de" created="Wed, 08 Apr 2026 16:35:19 GMT" type="link" url="https://firstpost.wpzz.de"/>
          <outline text="Next step: Install Baseline and needed plugins" created="Wed, 08 Apr 2026 16:35:48 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 7" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:30:44 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="07">
        <outline text="This evening: I fixed the Docker setup for the WordPress config" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 19:27:31 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="So I could connect to the site and do the one-click WordPress install" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 19:27:48 GMT"/>
          <outline text="ChatGPT set it up 95% correctly, but that last 5% is the fun part 😃" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 19:29:02 GMT"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Multisite WordPress" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:30:45 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="ChatGPT gave me a detailed compose file" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:31:48 GMT"/>
          <outline text="It was a little too detailed. The containers started but I can’t connect with the browser " created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:32:26 GMT"/>
          <outline text="I see the problem, I can look at it again tomorrow (WordPress config needs adjusting) " created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:33:36 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Dave, what domain did you have in mind for the sites?" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:34:30 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Wildcard certs are a little tricky with LetsEncrypt, as opposed to single sites" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:35:19 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Caddy needs an API key to write temporary DNS records, not all DNS providers support that " created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:37:23 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Cloudflare works well, I’ve been using it in my test" created="Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:39:11 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 6" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 07:07:52 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="06">
        <outline text="VPS Server ordered for Multisite WordPress" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 07:07:53 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="162.222.205.250, ionos.shanson.de" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 08:27:23 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Basic setup for ssh and docker completed" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 08:27:32 GMT">
            <outline text="Cloud config for docker (Hetzner)" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 08:28:03 GMT" type="link" url="https://gist.github.com/OnSive/21c9c12c73e8b230edef813958a7f433"/>
            <outline text="sshd didn't work out as expected, sshd.config had to be adjusted manually" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 08:29:31 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="That's all for today, it's a holiday and we're going on a long bike ride 🚴‍♂️" created="Mon, 06 Apr 2026 08:30:09 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 5" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:16:41 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="05">
        <outline text="Multisite WordPress" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:04:25 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="I'd like to start setting up the production server" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:04:58 GMT">
            <outline text="That will be quicker than setting up full test server, then moving everything over" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:14:34 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="8 GB RAM and 2 CPUs should be good for up to 20 sites" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:05:36 GMT">
            <outline text="Says ChatGPT" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:06:04 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="I can set up a server from IONOS for 6€/month (12 month commitment)" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:06:13 GMT">
            <outline text="https://www.ionos.com/servers/vps" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:08:53 GMT" type="link" url="https://www.ionos.com/servers/vps"/>
            <outline text="But it's cheaper to order from Germany 😃" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:09:14 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Dave, if that's OK I'll order the server and start setting it up" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:10:05 GMT"/>
          <outline text="We can then later move https://links.daveverse.org/ to the new server, then we don't need the jamaica server at DigitalOcean anymore" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 11:11:23 GMT"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Baseline: data-postid attributes " created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:16:42 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="I'm glad things are working, I'll close the issue" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:17:49 GMT"/>
          <outline text="The current implementation in Baseline is difficult to maintain" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:18:04 GMT">
            <outline text="The attributes are currently added directly in the layout templates" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:18:37 GMT"/>
            <outline text="It would be better if they were added in a separate function" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:19:28 GMT"/>
            <outline text="Then we can work on the layout without having to worry about breaking the attributes" created="Sun, 05 Apr 2026 10:19:47 GMT"/>
          </outline>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="April 1" created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:31:56 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="01">
        <outline text="MCP and WordPress" created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:31:57 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="Yes, I got Dave's mail. And the mail from WordPress.com " created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:32:02 GMT"/>
          <outline text="My first thought was that it looks like it's working over WP COM API, so it will probably work with Jetpack on self-hosted sites" created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:33:01 GMT"/>
          <outline text="I'm not sure why I'd want to do that. If I can already tell the API exactly what I want, why should I have have AI try to guess what I want. Especially since it often guesses wrong. " created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:34:03 GMT"/>
          <outline text="On the other hand, I get the marketing value. And that I don't immediately see the use case may be a lack of imagination on my part. 😃" created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:36:41 GMT"/>
          <outline text="I'll take a look at it and see if we can use it." created="Wed, 01 Apr 2026 14:38:10 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
    </outline>
    <outline text="March 2026" created="Mon, 02 Mar 2026 16:26:35 GMT" name="march2026" type="calendarMonth">
      <outline text="March 30" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2026 15:11:25 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="30">
        <outline text="re the source namespace declaration, what should we do?" created="Sun, 29 Mar 2026 14:44:32 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="I see Fernando beat us to it 😃" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2026 15:11:49 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="March 28" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:39:15 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="28">
        <outline text="CSS on daveverse.org - how should Dave make updates" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:39:16 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="Short answer - just keep editing https://s3.amazonaws.com/scripting.com/code/baselineplayground/testing.css  " created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:40:07 GMT">
            <outline text="Nothing should break (knock on wood and Murphy willing)" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:44:40 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Long answer - I merged the testing.css file into the CSS of the Baseline theme" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:41:52 GMT">
            <outline text="This way the theme has your changes without having to link to testing.css" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:42:40 GMT"/>
            <outline text="And everyone who has the latest version of the theme will have the CSS updates" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:43:21 GMT"/>
            <outline text="I'd prefer to have your CSS in the theme itself, that's why I merged in testing.css" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:44:34 GMT">
              <outline text="It would have been better to check in with you before merging... sorry about that." created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:50:35 GMT"/>
              <outline text="It can always be undone, thank git 😃" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:52:04 GMT"/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Go ahead and keep updating testing.css. " created="Sat, 28 Mar 2026 18:50:06 GMT"/>
          </outline>
        </outline>
      </outline>
      <outline text="March 26" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 13:35:13 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="26">
        <outline text="linkblog is back up!" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:36:22 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="MySQL had crashed somehow" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:36:55 GMT"/>
          <outline text="When restarted, all the .ibd files (where the data is stored) were locked" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:37:39 GMT"/>
          <outline text="Solution is to mv each .ibd file to ibd.bak, then cp it back to .db" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:38:00 GMT"/>
          <outline text="I have no idea why that works " created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:39:59 GMT">
            <outline text="Apparently copying the file removes the lock from the metadata" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:40:30 GMT"/>
            <outline text="https://serverfault.com/questions/477448/mysql-keeps-crashing-innodb-unable-to-lock-ibdata1-error-11" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:48:49 GMT" type="link" url="https://serverfault.com/questions/477448/mysql-keeps-crashing-innodb-unable-to-lock-ibdata1-error-11"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="I'll figure out what I learned from this episode once my blood pressure comes back down. 😃" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:52:38 GMT">
            <outline text="I had no idea whether the data would be lost or not." created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:53:12 GMT"/>
          </outline>
        </outline>
        <outline text="linkblog: &quot;Error establishing a database connection&quot;" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 13:35:14 GMT" type="outline">
          <outline text="MySQL has crashed, without MySQL WordPress cannot run" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:22:55 GMT"/>
          <outline text="MySQL is crashing with an error" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 13:35:21 GMT">
            <outline text="[ERROR] [MY-012574] [InnoDB] Unable to lock ./ibdata1 error: 11" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 13:35:44 GMT"/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Try stopping everything, and restarting MySQL (me, not Dave 😃)" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 13:35:50 GMT"/>
          <outline text="The database cannot be started, there are system level errors. It cannot open files from the file system. I'm working on them one by one." created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:15:39 GMT"/>
          <outline text="I am getting these errors repeatedly (even though the file mysql.idb is there)" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:17:48 GMT">
            <outline text="0 [System] [MY-015015] [Server] MySQL Server - start." created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:18:00 GMT"/>
            <outline text="0 [System] [MY-010116] [Server] /usr/sbin/mysqld (mysqld 8.4.8) starting as process 1"/>
            <outline text="1 [System] [MY-013576] [InnoDB] InnoDB initialization has started."/>
            <outline text="1 [ERROR] [MY-012592] [InnoDB] Operating system error number 2 in a file operation."/>
            <outline text="1 [ERROR] [MY-012593] [InnoDB] The error means the system cannot find the path specified."/>
            <outline text="1 [ERROR] [MY-012216] [InnoDB] Cannot open datafile for read-only: 'mysql.ibd' OS error: 71"/>
            <outline text="mysqld: Can't open file: 'mysql.ibd' (errno: 0 - )" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:18:53 GMT"/>
            <outline text="1 [ERROR] [MY-010334] [Server] Failed to initialize DD Storage Engine"/>
            <outline text="0 [ERROR] [MY-010020] [Server] Data Dictionary initialization failed."/>
            <outline text="0 [ERROR] [MY-010119] [Server] Aborting"/>
            <outline text="0 [System] [MY-010910] [Server] /usr/sbin/mysqld: Shutdown complete (mysqld 8.4.8)  MySQL Community Server - GPL."/>
            <outline text="0 [System] [MY-015016] [Server] MySQL Server - end."/>
          </outline>
          <outline text="Operator error! I had named mysql.idb incorrectly! It's supposed to be mysql.ibd. 🤦‍♂️" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2026 14:36:02 GMT"/>
        </outline>
      </outline>
